    %% Machine Status State Diagram
    %% Source of truth for this diagram: docs/design/machine-schema.md section 4
    %% Referenced (linked, not embedded) from: docs/design/machine-schema.md
    %% SCOPE: shows every event's effect from every state, including self-loops
    %% where a lower-or-equal-severity event is blocked from lowering status
    %% (machine-schema.md section 4.2). Multiple blocked/no-op reasons for the
    %% same state are combined into one self-loop label rather than drawn as
    %% separate stacked arrows, to keep the diagram legible.
    %% STATUS_CHANGED is deliberately NOT drawn as 20 individual any-to-any
    %% arrows — its rule ("always overwrites, bypasses ranking entirely") is
    %% uniform across all states and adding 20 near-identical arrows would
    %% drown out the more informative severity-based transitions above. It is
    %% called out once via a note instead.
    %% VERSIONING: update in place; do not fork per phase (see architecture.mmd).
    [*] --> IDLE

    IDLE --> RUNNING: PRODUCTION_COMPLETED
    IDLE --> WARNING: TEMPERATURE_REPORTED (over threshold)
    IDLE --> ERROR: ERROR_OCCURRED
    IDLE --> MAINTENANCE: MAINTENANCE_REQUIRED

    RUNNING --> RUNNING: PRODUCTION_COMPLETED (same rank)
    RUNNING --> WARNING: TEMPERATURE_REPORTED (over threshold)
    RUNNING --> ERROR: ERROR_OCCURRED
    RUNNING --> MAINTENANCE: MAINTENANCE_REQUIRED

    WARNING --> WARNING: TEMPERATURE_REPORTED (same rank) / PRODUCTION_COMPLETED (blocked, lower rank — healthScore delta still applies)
    WARNING --> ERROR: ERROR_OCCURRED
    WARNING --> MAINTENANCE: MAINTENANCE_REQUIRED

    MAINTENANCE --> MAINTENANCE: TEMPERATURE_REPORTED (blocked) / MAINTENANCE_REQUIRED (same rank) / PRODUCTION_COMPLETED (blocked)
    MAINTENANCE --> ERROR: ERROR_OCCURRED

    ERROR --> ERROR: TEMPERATURE_REPORTED (blocked) / ERROR_OCCURRED (same rank) / MAINTENANCE_REQUIRED (blocked) / PRODUCTION_COMPLETED (blocked)

    note right of ERROR
        STATUS_CHANGED bypasses severity ranking
        entirely: payload.currentStatus always
        overwrites, moving ANY state to ANY other
        state. It is the only way to recover a
        machine from ERROR or MAINTENANCE back to
        RUNNING/IDLE.
    end note
